ttp://www.seiryuu.org/~suikoden/Navigation/soul_s.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic collecting dust?</span><hr size=1> I like to consider myself fairly old time, but I don't think the epics were meant to span expansions in the sense that they would *always* be the be-all-and-end-all. Epics were introduced not too long before Velious release, i.e. the quests were of a Kunark level. Now, for that time, they were almost without exception *THE* best, all the time. As such, the quests themselves are balanced (in the loosest sense of the word.. some too easy, some too hard) for a Kunarkian level. So, a high-end Kunark quest yields a high-end Kunark reward. (Or in the case of the Rogue epic, a high-end old world quest yields a high-end Kunark reward.)<br>
<br>
If the weapon was to beat the items available in Velious' endgame and Luclin's endgame it would be phenomonally overpowered considering what's needed to get one, i.e. not *too* much by today's standards. If they were to do this the quests would have to be upgraded and that would mean the Kunark level players would be denied their final quests.<br>
<br>
Making the RB range slot usable would make the *best* Rogue range item in EQ trivial to get *CONSIDERING IT'S THE BEST RANGE SLOT ITEM* (No, I'm not saying it's a &quot;freebringer&quot;, I'm saying if it was made Range-usable it would be FAR too good for the level of the quest- REPEAT, IT'S NOT A FREEBRINGER.) Best to leave it as it is.<br>
<br>
Oh, and the Freebringer thing? I chortled mightily when a Shaman friend remarked this the other day. Wow, the Shaman epic sure is difficult too. My small-ass guild had a Shaman epic at level 50, and the Shaman in question didn't even play much. The sole hard component in the Shaman quest is the Fear bottleneck, and it's not even that bad compared to the Ranger, Enchanter planar components. Funny how these buzzwords are thrown around without really thinking about them. Sure, the Rogue epic is easy but there's two others just as simple. <p><p><b><font face="Tahoma" size="5"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48384">Jokah Pandahunter</a><br>
